The paper deals with the design and analysis of memory hard functions, which are a cryptographic primitive used in various applications. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new type of memory hard function, which involves computational independence, and analyzes its complexity. This involves computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of memory architectures such as RAM and cache, which falls under the category of computer systems and networking (cs.SE) and information theory (cs.IT).
